data.description: LOOKING FOR A NICE HOME CLOSE TO LAKE PAGOSA? OWNERS PRIDE!! This LIGHT AND BRIGHT 1300 sq. ft. single level 3 bedroom 2 bath 2 car garage home is in the perfect location and just a hop skip and a jump from the fishing docs. Great floorplan with open living area complete with a cozy gas fireplace to snuggle up in front of on the cold winter nights, nice size kitchen with newer stainless appliances (2918), gas cooking stove, double glass doors leading to a fantastic private back patio great for summer enjoyment and a beautiful back yard with mature Aspen tree's, Ponderosa's and mature landscaping. Primary bedroom is the perfect size with on suite bathroom and walk in shower, the other 2 bedrooms are nice size and the full guest bath is a real plus. The garage is oversized with utility sink and plenty of storage, the laundry room is located right off the garage and the washer and dryer are fairly new. New carpet and paint in primary bedroom along with new flooring in bathrooms and hall way in 2020. Home under went a major remodel in 2018. New roof in 2020. NEW PAVED DRIVEWAY AND WALKWAY 2022. The Pagosa Lakes area offers a paved trail system for bike riding or walking. The recreation center is a 2 million dollar facility with all the state of the art exercise equipment, saltwater pool, hot tub and more. The Wyndham tennis courts are also available for Pagosa Lakes Property Owners. Less than 10min. to down town historic Pagosa Springs home of the deepest hot springs in the world where you can soak in luxury, walk along the San Juan River, hike the Reservoir Hill or take in one of the trendy restaurants or brew pubs. Enjoy the 2.5 million plus acres of the San Juan National Forest just minutes in almost any direction you drive, bike or hike . Home is back on the market due to Conditional Sale property not selling?
